<body style="padding: 3px 10px;">
<%= render 'worker_mailer/lead_milestones' %>	
<p>Hey <%= first_name @user.name %>, here's today's leads.</p>
<%= render 'worker_mailer/lead_render' %>
<%= render 'worker_mailer/lead_categories' %>
<br>
<h3>These leads have been hand-checked for quality.</h3> 
<p>If you see something you don&rsquo;t like, let me know. Mistakes happen and errors do get in but I&rsquo;d hate to see you go back to elance or checking job boards manually because of an error. We want to know about anything you'd like to see removed.
<br>
<a href="MAILTO:julie@letsworkshop.com?subject=RE: Workshop lead error?&body=Hello Julie! I didn't like seeing this lead: { insert lead } because it { insert reason for disatisfaction }. I'd prefer to get something that was more { insert relevant benefit }. Thank you!">Report an error</a></p>
<br>
<h3>Want something else?</h3>
<p>Premium-members now have access to leads found just for them. Use the form below to get really specific about what you're looking for and we'll try to include it in the next batch of leads.</p>
<p><a href="https://workshopmastercraft.wufoo.com/forms/workshop-lead-request/">Send lead request</a> (premium-only)</p>
<br>
<h3>Overwhelmed?</h3>
<p>I'm Julie, your personal email specialist. I'm here to help you land one of these projects. So let me know how can I help and where are you currently getting stuck. Whether it's choosing a lead, writing something great or anything else we'll get it straightened out.<br>
<a href="MAILTO:julie@letsworkshop.com">Email Julie</a></p>
<br>
<h3>Unsure about a lead?</h3> 
<p>Remember, contacting just one new opportunity per day comes out to over 20 per month. There's probably no "ideal client" in this email but pick the closest one and send them a quick email. What's the worst that can happen?</p>
<br>
<h3>Need to find a freelancer?</h3>
<p><a href="http://app.letsworkshop.com/connect">Post your project</a></p>
<p style="border-top: 1px solid #eeeeee; padding: 2em 0; margin: 2em 0; font-size: 90%;"><a href="<%= edit_user_registration_url(only_path: false) %>">Update your account</a></p>
